utte county", "freight trains", "color", "alliance", "united states"], "timestamp": "2022-08-02T18:36:27.081Z", "title": "Coal trains near Alliance in Box Butte County, Nebraska", "type": ["still image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2021757853/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2021757808", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021757808/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/highsm.69587", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/highsm.69587/", "https://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2021757808/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2021757808/", "https://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/highsm/item/2021757808/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/highsm/item/2021757808/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/highsm.69587"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["highsmith, carol m."], "date": "2021-01-01", "dates": ["2021"], "description": ["Title, date, and keywords based on information provided by the photographer. Farmer and engineer Jim Reinders built the array of old automobiles, obtained from nearby farms and dumps and scrapyards, as a tribute to his father. At first the city lobbied to tear the odd monument down, then put a fence around it, but eventually embraced it and called Alliance the \"Home of Carhenge.\" Purchase Carol M. Highsmith Photography, Inc.; 2021  (DLC/PP-2021:107). Forms part of Carol M. Highsmith's America Project in the Carol M. Highsmith Archive. Credit Line: Photographs in Carol M. Highsmith's America Project in the Carol M. Highsmith Archive, Library of Congress, Prints and Photographs Division."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2022-08-02T18:21:49.396Z", "group": ["catalog", "highsm", "catalog-split-08", "main-catalog", "carol-m-highsmith", "main-catalog-split-08"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021757808/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/highsm/69500/69587_150px.jpg#h=76&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/highsm/69500/69587r.jpg#h=323&w=640", "https://tile